  </ul>

  <!-- ═══ FAQ ═══ -->
  <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
  <div class="dcf-faq">
    <details>
      <summary>Why use DCF?</summary>
      <div class="dcf-faq-answer">DCF forces you to state explicit assumptions about growth and risk, then lets math determine the price. It directly connects cash flow generation to value.</div>
    </details>
    <details>
      <summary>How were assumptions derived?</summary>
      <div class="dcf-faq-answer">Discount rate uses the 10Y Treasury and standard equity risk premium. Growth rates are bounded based on actual historical Free Cash Flow CAGRs.</div>
    </details>
  </div>

